        "id": 1002885
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-05T17:54:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is not blocking.\nThe dispatch handler `completion_method_instance::operator()` returns 1 without calling `method_return()`; \nso the dispatch is released immediately and the reply is transmitted later from `completion::send()` on whatever callback completes the work. \nThis is the same mechanism the coroutine path already uses, and the completion path just swaps the coroutine for a caller-owned completion.",
      "parentUuid": "fd124172_5e84a0cb",
      "revId": "112efbf16367f0bab8d994b200cd7ba8822239be",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
